---
// About Preview Section Component
---

<section id="about" class="about-preview">
	<div class="container">
		<div class="about-hero">
			<picture>
				<img src="/ellie-hq.jpg" alt="Ellie Cullity, midwife and lactation consultant, smiling" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
			</picture>
		</div>
		<div class="about-content">
			<h2>Meet Ellie Cullity</h2>
			<p class="intro">
				Behind The Golden Hour Co is Ellie Cullity, an experienced registered nurse, midwife, 
				International Board Certified Lactation Consultant (IBCLC), and childbirth educator. 
				As a mother of two young children herself, Ellie brings both professional expertise and 
				lived experience to every family she supports.
			</p>
			<p>
				Based in Fremantle, Ellie serves families throughout the Perth metropolitan area with 
				evidence-based, compassionate care that honours your unique journey into parenthood. 
				She understands firsthand the joys and challenges of early parenthood, and combines her 
				clinical knowledge with empathy and practical wisdom.
			</p>
			<p>
				Every family deserves informed support, continuous care, and the confidence to make decisions 
				that are right for them. Ellie is here to walk alongside you, from pregnancy through the precious 
				early weeks with your baby.
			</p>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>

<style>
	.about-preview {
		padding: var(--spacing-2xl) 0;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #F5F1E8 0%, #EDE7D9 100%);
	}
	
	.about-content {
		max-width: 800px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		text-align: center;
	}
	
	.about-content h2 {
		color: var(--color-primary-dark);
		margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
	}
	
	.about-content p {
		font-size: 1.125rem;
		color: var(--color-text-light);
		line-height: 1.8;
	}
	
	.about-content p.intro {
		font-size: 1.25rem;
		font-weight: 500;
		color: var(--color-primary-dark);
		margin-bottom: var(--spacing-lg);
	}

	/* Hero image styles */
	.about-hero {
		max-width: 650px;
		margin: 0 auto var(--spacing-lg);
		overflow: hidden;
		border-radius: 12px;
	}

	.about-hero img {
		display: block;
		width: 100%;
		height: auto;
		/* make sure she doesn't get huge */
		max-height: 55vh;
		/* make sure her face doesn't get chopped in half */
		min-height: 500px;
		object-fit: cover;
		/* keep the top of the image visible when cropping */
		object-position: top;
	}
</style>
